Package com.google.api.client.googleapis.auth.authsub

Google's legacy AuthSub authorization as specified in AuthSub for Web Applications .

This package depends on the com.google.api.client.auth, com.google.api.client.googleapis, com.google.api.client.googleapis.auth, com.google.api.client.http and com.google.api.client.util packages.

Warning: this package is experimental, and its content may be changed in incompatible ways or possibly entirely removed in a future version of the library

@since 21.20
Class AuthSub

@since 21.2 0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class AuthSubHelper

AuthSub token manager for a single user.

To properly initialize, set:

  • .setToken: single-use or session token (required)
  • .transport: Google transport (recommended)
  • .privateKey: private key for secure AuthSub (recommended)
@since 21.2 0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class AuthSubHelper, void setPrivateKey(PrivateKey)

Sets to the given private key for secure AuthSub or {@code null} for non-secure AuthSub.

Updates the authorization header of the Google transport (set using .setTransport(GoogleTransportHttpTransport)).

Class AuthSubHelper, void setToken(String)

Sets to the given single-use or session token (or resets any existing token if {@code null}).

Any previous stored single-use or session token will be forgotten. Updates the authorization header of the Google transport (set using .setTransport(GoogleTransportHttpTransport)).

Class AuthSubSingleUseTokenRequestUrl

Generic URL that builds an AuthSub request URL to retrieve a single-use token. See documentation. @since 21.2 0 @author Yaniv Inbar
